<?xml version="1.0"?>
<entry xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>More Smilies 2.0</title><author><name>Matt Read</name></author><link rel="alternate" href="https://mattread.com/more-smilies-20"/><link rel="edit" href="https://mattread.com/more-smilies-20/atom"/><id>http://mattread.com/archives/2006/01/more-smilies-20/</id><updated>2007-04-06T14:58:21-04:00</updated><app:edited xmlns:app="http://www.w3.org/2007/app">2013-03-08T22:58:25-05:00</app:edited><published>2005-12-31T19:13:43-05:00</published><category term="announcements"/><category term="wordpress-plugin"/><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://mattread.com/projects/wp-plugins/more-smilies-plugin/"&gt;More Smilies 2.0&lt;/a&gt; is out, :!: and now has clickable smilies for the comments form (with a little edit), and clickable smilies for the admin area (no editing required). It even supports the WYSIWYG editor thanks to &lt;a href="http://asymptomatic.net"&gt;Owen's&lt;/a&gt; buttonsnap library.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;2.0 Also supports Owen's &lt;a href="http://redalt.com/wiki/Role+Manager"&gt;Role Manager&lt;/a&gt; plugin. It adds the new capability, 'change_smilies'. So if you use Role Manager, you will need to assign the 'change_smilies' capability to the various roles, or you won't be able to change smilies. :)&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;Oh, and one more important note. It's only for WordPress 2.0. Do not install it on 1.5 or the sky will fall on your head. And that could hurt.&lt;/p&gt;</content></entry>
